  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid response to the Ebola virus disease (EVD) outbreack in Nord Kivu province in the Democratic Republic of Congo.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health assistance to vulnerable communities in regions affected by, and those at risk of, Ebola. This WHO project supports early detection, contact training, and active search of Ebola Virus Disease cases; improving infection prevention and control measures in health facilities; and providing medical care for Ebola patients. The project provides life-saving assistance to 187,750 people, including 50,690 women, 46,330 men, 90,120 children, and 28,000 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
